			        Cloudera Production Deployment
1] Update the server
2] Disabling THP
3] Install NTP
4] Set Swappiness
5] Setting root reserved Space
6] Save the instance to an image
7] Preparing external database for cloudera 
8] Install MySQL
9] Move innodb log file
10] Edit the option file my.cnf to Cloudera recommended settings
11] Make MySQL Start on boot
12] Start MySQL
13] MySQL Secure installation
14] Install MySQL JDBC driver
15] Establish your CM Repository
16] sudo apt-get update
17] Install CM Server software
18] Install Oracle JDK
19] Install the CM Server Pacakages
20] Setting up the CM Server database
21] start the CM Server 
22] Setup custom CDH Repository [cd /opt/cloudera/parcel-repo]
23] Restart CM Server
24] Login to CM webUI on 7180
25] Create database for CDH Services
26] Add MySQL driver jar
27] For HUE [nano my.cnf]-[MySQL]-bind-address=0.0.0.0 SQL-mod=STRICT_ALL_TABLES
28] sudo Service MySQL restart
29] Install MySQL JDBC jar on hosts where services are running
30] Now continue installation on CM webUI
